cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on fine-tuning pre-trained language models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new computational framework that involves regularization and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using the framework for image captioning, which could indicate a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions preventing knowledge forgetting, which could suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
